(function () {
  window.I18N = window.I18N || {};
  window.I18N["en"] = Object.assign(window.I18N["en"] || {}, {"common.nav.home":"Home","common.nav.prerequisites":"Prerequisites","common.nav.startCoding":"Start Coding with AI","common.nav.proFeatures":"Copilot Pro Features","common.nav.extendedCapabilities":"Extended Capabilities","common.nav.specDriven":"Spec-Driven Development","common.nav.agenticWorkflows":"Agentic Workflows","common.nav.ariaMain":"Main navigation","common.theme.dark":"Dark","common.theme.light":"Light","common.theme.toggleAria":"Toggle dark mode","common.lang.selectAria":"Select language","common.lang.label":"Language","common.stepNav.previous":"Previous","common.stepNav.next":"Next","common.stepNav.previousAria":"Previous step","common.stepNav.nextAria":"Next step","common.sidebar.toggleAria":"Toggle navigation menu","common.sidebar.stepsAria":"Workshop steps","common.footer.html":"DevAI Day Workshop &bull; <a href=\"https://github.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">GitHub</a> &bull; Built with ❤️ for developers","spec-driven-development.meta.title":"Spec-Driven Development - DevAI Day Workshop","spec-driven-development.meta.description":"Learn Spec-Driven Development with GitHub Copilot — write specs first, then let AI plan, break down tasks, and implement using GitHub Spec Kit.","spec-driven-development.sidebar.backToHome":"Back to Home","spec-driven-development.sidebar.title":"Spec-Driven Development","spec-driven-development.sidebar.step1":"What is Spec-Driven Development?","spec-driven-development.sidebar.step2":"Writing Specs with Copilot","spec-driven-development.sidebar.step3":"Introducing GitHub Spec Kit","spec-driven-development.sidebar.step4":"The Spec Kit Workflow","spec-driven-development.sidebar.step5":"Hands-on: Build a Feature Spec-First","spec-driven-development.progress.label":"Progress","spec-driven-development.step1.duration":"15 minutes","spec-driven-development.step2.duration":"20 minutes","spec-driven-development.step3.duration":"20 minutes","spec-driven-development.step4.duration":"25 minutes","spec-driven-development.step5.duration":"30 minutes","spec-driven-development.stepNav.aria":"Step navigation","spec-driven-development.step5.nextAgentic":"Next: Agentic Workflows","spec-driven-development.step1.span1":"Step 1 of 5","spec-driven-development.step1.title":"What is Spec-Driven Development?","spec-driven-development.step1.p2":"Spec-Driven Development (SDD) flips the usual AI coding workflow. Instead of prompting an agent to \"just build it\" and hoping the result matches your intent, you first capture <strong>what</strong> you want and <strong>why</strong> in a clear specification — then let Copilot turn that spec into a plan, tasks, and code.","spec-driven-development.step1.h21":"Intent vs. Implementation","spec-driven-development.step1.p3":"Traditional prompting mixes intent and implementation together in a single throwaway message. Spec-driven development separates them:","spec-driven-development.step1.li1":"<strong>Intent (the spec)</strong> — The durable description of the problem, the desired behavior, constraints, and acceptance criteria. It is reviewed, versioned, and shared.","spec-driven-development.step1.li2":"<strong>Implementation (the code)</strong> — A consequence of the spec, generated by the agent and regenerated when the spec changes.","spec-driven-development.step1.p4":"When the spec is the source of truth, the code becomes easier to regenerate, review, and reason about — and the AI has a stable target to aim at.","spec-driven-development.step1.h22":"Why Specs Matter for AI Coding","spec-driven-development.step1.li3":"<strong>Better results</strong> — Agents perform dramatically better with explicit requirements than with vague one-liners.","spec-driven-development.step1.li4":"<strong>Shared understanding</strong> — A spec is reviewable by humans before a single line of code is written.","spec-driven-development.step1.li5":"<strong>Reproducibility</strong> — The same spec can drive consistent regeneration across models and sessions.","spec-driven-development.step1.li6":"<strong>Guardrails</strong> — Constraints and acceptance criteria keep the agent from wandering off scope.","spec-driven-development.step1.strong1":"Mental model","spec-driven-development.step1.p5":"Think of the spec as the <em>contract</em> and the agent as the <em>contractor</em>. You refine the contract until it is unambiguous; the contractor builds to it.","spec-driven-development.step1.h23":"When to Use SDD","spec-driven-development.step1.li7":"<strong>Use it</strong> for new features, multi-file changes, and anything you'll need to review, hand off, or revisit.","spec-driven-development.step1.li8":"<strong>Skip it</strong> for trivial edits, quick experiments, or single-line fixes where the overhead isn't worth it.","spec-driven-development.step1.h24":"The SDD Loop","spec-driven-development.step1.li9":"<strong>Specify</strong> — Describe what and why (not how).","spec-driven-development.step1.li10":"<strong>Plan</strong> — Let Copilot propose a technical approach.","spec-driven-development.step1.li11":"<strong>Break down</strong> — Decompose the plan into concrete, ordered tasks.","spec-driven-development.step1.li12":"<strong>Implement</strong> — Execute the tasks, verifying against acceptance criteria.","spec-driven-development.step1.p6":"Over the next steps you'll practice this loop first with plain Copilot, then with <strong>GitHub Spec Kit</strong> — a toolkit that formalizes each stage with slash commands.","spec-driven-development.step1.strong2":"Try it (2 min): Intent vs. implementation","spec-driven-development.step1.p7":"Take a feature you recently built and write a single sentence describing its <em>intent</em> (the what and why) with <strong>zero</strong> mention of <em>how</em> it was built. If you can't avoid naming a function, framework, or data structure, rewrite it. This is the muscle SDD trains.","spec-driven-development.step2.span1":"Step 2 of 5","spec-driven-development.step2.title":"Writing Specs with Copilot","spec-driven-development.step2.p2":"Before reaching for dedicated tooling, you can practice spec-driven development with nothing more than a markdown file and GitHub Copilot. The goal: a spec precise enough that Copilot can implement it without guessing.","spec-driven-development.step2.h21":"Anatomy of a Good Spec","spec-driven-development.step2.p3":"A useful feature spec is structured and testable. A simple template:","spec-driven-development.step2.strong1":"Describe what, not how","spec-driven-development.step2.p4":"Keep specs focused on behavior and outcomes. Leave the implementation details (frameworks, file layout, algorithms) to the planning step so the agent can choose the best fit for your codebase.","spec-driven-development.step2.h22":"Use Plan Mode to Turn a Spec into a Plan","spec-driven-development.step2.p5":"Copilot's <strong>Plan Mode</strong> reads your spec and the surrounding codebase, then proposes an implementation plan for you to review <em>before</em> any code is written. This is the bridge between intent and implementation.","spec-driven-development.step2.li1":"Open your repository in VS Code with the spec file visible.","spec-driven-development.step2.li2":"Start a Copilot Chat session in Plan Mode and reference the spec: <code>Plan the implementation of #file:cart-discounts.md</code>","spec-driven-development.step2.li3":"Review the proposed steps, push back on anything that doesn't fit, and iterate until the plan matches your intent.","spec-driven-development.step2.h23":"Persist Conventions with Instructions Files","spec-driven-development.step2.p6":"Specs describe a single feature; <strong>instructions files</strong> describe how <em>all</em> work in the repo should be done. Together they give the agent both the \"what\" and the \"house rules\".","spec-driven-development.step2.strong2":"Try it (3 min): Sharpen one acceptance criterion","spec-driven-development.step2.p7":"Look at the discount-code spec above. Add <strong>one</strong> more acceptance criterion that pins down an edge case it currently misses (for example: what happens when a code is applied to an empty cart?). Phrase it as a concrete, checkable assertion — a value in, a value out.","spec-driven-development.step2.p8":"You can also scope guidance with path-specific <code>.instructions.md</code> files so different parts of the codebase follow different rules.","spec-driven-development.step2.h24":"Exercise: Write and Plan a Spec","spec-driven-development.step2.li4":"Create <code>specs/feature.md</code> using the template above for a small feature in a sample repo.","spec-driven-development.step2.li5":"Add a <code>.github/copilot-instructions.md</code> with 3–4 conventions for the repo.","spec-driven-development.step2.li6":"Ask Copilot in Plan Mode to plan the implementation from your spec.","spec-driven-development.step2.li7":"Refine the spec until the generated plan is correct — notice how clearer specs produce better plans.","spec-driven-development.step3.span1":"Step 3 of 5","spec-driven-development.step3.title":"Introducing GitHub Spec Kit","spec-driven-development.step3.p2":"<a href=\"https://github.com/github/spec-kit\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub Spec Kit</a> is an open-source toolkit that turns the spec-driven loop into a repeatable workflow. It adds a set of slash commands to your AI coding agent and a project structure that keeps specs, plans, and tasks organized.","spec-driven-development.step3.h21":"What Spec Kit Gives You","spec-driven-development.step3.li1":"<strong>A consistent structure</strong> — Dedicated locations for your project constitution, specs, plans, and task lists.","spec-driven-development.step3.li2":"<strong>Slash commands</strong> — <code>/speckit.constitution</code>, <code>/speckit.specify</code>, <code>/speckit.plan</code>, <code>/speckit.tasks</code>, and <code>/speckit.implement</code> that drive each stage of the loop.","spec-driven-development.step3.li3":"<strong>Agent-agnostic</strong> — Works with GitHub Copilot and 30+ other coding agents.","spec-driven-development.step3.strong1":"Prerequisites","spec-driven-development.step3.li4":"<strong>Python 3.11+</strong> and <a href=\"https://docs.astral.sh/uv/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><code>uv</code></a> installed","spec-driven-development.step3.li5":"<strong>Git</strong> and a <strong>GitHub Copilot</strong>-enabled agent (e.g., VS Code or Copilot CLI)","spec-driven-development.step3.h22":"Install the specify CLI & Initialize a Project","spec-driven-development.step3.p3":"Install the <code>specify</code> CLI with <code>uv</code>, then scaffold a project and choose your agent with <code>--integration</code>. Replace <code>vX.Y.Z</code> with the latest <a href=\"https://github.com/github/spec-kit/releases\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">release tag</a>:","spec-driven-development.step3.p4":"Spec Kit adds its <code>/speckit.*</code> commands and a <code>.specify/</code> + <code>specs/</code> structure. In IDE agents the commands appear as slash commands; in <strong>GitHub Copilot CLI</strong> you select the agent with <code>/agents</code> (or address it directly in a prompt).","spec-driven-development.step3.h23":"Define the Project Constitution","spec-driven-development.step3.p5":"The <strong>constitution</strong> captures the non-negotiable principles your project must always follow — quality bars, architectural rules, testing expectations. The agent consults it during planning and implementation.","spec-driven-development.step3.p6":"Spec Kit writes these principles to a constitution file so every subsequent <code>/speckit.plan</code> and <code>/speckit.implement</code> stays aligned with them.","spec-driven-development.step3.strong2":"Try it (5 min): Scaffold and inspect","spec-driven-development.step3.p7":"Run <code>specify init</code> on a throwaway project and open the generated <code>.specify/</code> and <code>specs/</code> folders. Then run a <code>/speckit.constitution</code> command with two principles of your own and open the resulting constitution file. What did Spec Kit add that you didn't type?","spec-driven-development.step3.strong3":"Constitution vs. instructions","spec-driven-development.step3.p8":"A Spec Kit constitution plays a similar role to a <code>copilot-instructions.md</code> file — project-wide rules — but it is woven into Spec Kit's structured planning commands so the principles are enforced at each stage.","spec-driven-development.step4.span1":"Step 4 of 5","spec-driven-development.step4.title":"The Spec Kit Workflow","spec-driven-development.step4.p2":"With a constitution in place, Spec Kit drives the rest of the loop through its <code>/speckit.*</code> commands. Each one produces a reviewable artifact you can refine before moving on.","spec-driven-development.step4.h21":"/speckit.specify — Describe What and Why","spec-driven-development.step4.p3":"Start with the feature, focused on intent rather than the tech stack. Spec Kit generates a structured specification file.","spec-driven-development.step4.h22":"/speckit.plan — Choose the Technical Approach","spec-driven-development.step4.p4":"Now provide your stack and constraints. Spec Kit produces a technical plan that respects both your spec and your constitution.","spec-driven-development.step4.h23":"/speckit.tasks — Break the Plan into Steps","spec-driven-development.step4.p5":"Decompose the plan into an ordered, actionable task list. This is where the work becomes concrete and trackable.","spec-driven-development.step4.p6":"Review the generated tasks for correct ordering and dependencies. Reorder or split anything that's too large before implementing.","spec-driven-development.step4.h24":"/speckit.implement — Execute the Tasks","spec-driven-development.step4.p7":"Have the agent work through the task list, building the feature against the spec and constitution.","spec-driven-development.step4.strong1":"Iterate at the right level","spec-driven-development.step4.p8":"If something is wrong, fix the <em>earliest</em> artifact that's wrong — update the spec, re-plan, regenerate tasks — rather than patching generated code by hand. Keeping the spec as the source of truth is what makes the workflow repeatable.","spec-driven-development.step4.h25":"Optional Quality Commands","spec-driven-development.step4.p9":"Spec Kit adds commands that act like \"unit tests for your spec\" — use them to catch gaps before you generate code:","spec-driven-development.step4.li1":"<code>/speckit.clarify</code> — Surface and resolve underspecified areas (run <em>before</em> <code>/speckit.plan</code>).","spec-driven-development.step4.li2":"<code>/speckit.analyze</code> — Cross-artifact consistency &amp; coverage check (run after <code>/speckit.tasks</code>, before <code>/speckit.implement</code>).","spec-driven-development.step4.li3":"<code>/speckit.checklist</code> — Generate a custom quality checklist validating requirement completeness, clarity, and consistency.","spec-driven-development.step4.strong2":"Try it (5 min): One command in isolation","spec-driven-development.step4.p10":"Before the full hands-on, practice a single stage on its own. In a project that already has a spec, run just <code>/speckit.tasks</code> and read the generated task list. Are the tasks ordered correctly? Is any single task too big to implement safely? Reorder or split one before moving on.","spec-driven-development.step4.h26":"The Full Loop at a Glance","spec-driven-development.step5.span1":"Step 5 of 5","spec-driven-development.step5.title":"Hands-on: Build a Feature Spec-First","spec-driven-development.step5.p2":"Put the full loop together. You'll take a small feature from idea to working code entirely spec-first, using Spec Kit.","spec-driven-development.step5.h21":"The Challenge","spec-driven-development.step5.p3":"Build a <strong>command-line \"habit tracker\"</strong> that lets a user add daily habits, mark them complete for today, and view a weekly streak summary. No UI framework required — keep it simple.","spec-driven-development.step5.h22":"Step-by-Step","spec-driven-development.step5.li1":"<strong>Initialize</strong> a fresh project with <code>specify init habit-tracker --integration copilot</code>.","spec-driven-development.step5.li2":"<strong>/speckit.constitution</strong> — Require unit tests for all logic, no external dependencies beyond the standard library, and clear help output.","spec-driven-development.step5.li3":"<strong>/speckit.specify</strong> — Describe the habit tracker's behavior and acceptance criteria (add, complete, weekly streak). Focus on what, not how.","spec-driven-development.step5.li4":"<strong>/speckit.plan</strong> — Choose a language (e.g., Python or Node), a storage approach (a local JSON file), and a simple command structure.","spec-driven-development.step5.li5":"<strong>/speckit.tasks</strong> — Generate the task list and review the ordering.","spec-driven-development.step5.li6":"<strong>/speckit.implement</strong> — Let the agent build it, then run the app and tests.","spec-driven-development.step5.h23":"Acceptance Criteria to Verify","spec-driven-development.step5.li7":"Adding a habit persists it across runs.","spec-driven-development.step5.li8":"Marking a habit complete twice in one day is idempotent.","spec-driven-development.step5.li9":"The weekly summary shows the correct current streak per habit.","spec-driven-development.step5.li10":"All logic is covered by passing unit tests.","spec-driven-development.step5.strong1":"Reflection","spec-driven-development.step5.p4":"When a criterion fails, resist hand-editing the code. Update the spec or plan and regenerate. Notice how much faster iteration becomes when the spec — not the code — is your source of truth.","spec-driven-development.step5.h31":"What's Next?","spec-driven-development.step5.li11":"Add a new requirement to the spec (e.g., reminders) and watch how a single <code>/speckit.plan</code> → <code>/speckit.tasks</code> → <code>/speckit.implement</code> pass extends the app.","spec-driven-development.step5.li12":"Combine SDD with the <a href=\"agentic-workflows.html\">Agentic Workflows</a> path to automate spec-driven changes in CI.","spec-driven-development.step5.li13":"Bring Spec Kit into a real repository and trial it on your next feature.","spec-driven-development.step5.h32":"Resources","spec-driven-development.step5.li14":"<a href=\"https://github.com/github/spec-kit\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub Spec Kit repository</a>","spec-driven-development.step5.li15":"<a href=\"https://github.blog/ai-and-ml/generative-ai/spec-driven-development-with-ai-get-started-with-a-new-open-source-toolkit/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Spec-driven development with AI (GitHub Blog)</a>","spec-driven-development.step5.li16":"<a href=\"https://docs.github.com/copilot\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub Copilot Documentation</a>","spec-driven-development.step5.li17":"<a href=\"https://docs.astral.sh/uv/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">uv / uvx documentation</a>"});
  window.I18N["nl"] = Object.assign(window.I18N["nl"] || {}, {"common.nav.home":"Home","common.nav.prerequisites":"Vereisten","common.nav.startCoding":"Beginnen met AI-coderen","common.nav.proFeatures":"Copilot Pro-functies","common.nav.extendedCapabilities":"Uitgebreide mogelijkheden","common.nav.specDriven":"Spec-gedreven ontwikkeling","common.nav.agenticWorkflows":"Agentische workflows","common.nav.ariaMain":"Hoofdnavigatie","common.theme.dark":"Donker","common.theme.light":"Licht","common.theme.toggleAria":"Donkere modus schakelen","common.lang.selectAria":"Taal selecteren","common.lang.label":"Taal","common.stepNav.previous":"Vorige","common.stepNav.next":"Volgende","common.stepNav.previousAria":"Vorige stap","common.stepNav.nextAria":"Volgende stap","common.sidebar.toggleAria":"Navigatiemenu schakelen","common.sidebar.stepsAria":"Workshopstappen","common.footer.html":"DevAI Day Workshop &bull; <a href=\"https://github.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">GitHub</a> &bull; Met ❤️ gemaakt voor ontwikkelaars","spec-driven-development.meta.title":"Spec-Driven Development - DevAI Day-workshop","spec-driven-development.meta.description":"Leer Spec-Driven Development met GitHub Copilot — schrijf eerst specs en laat AI daarna plannen, tasks opsplitsen en implementeren met GitHub Spec Kit.","spec-driven-development.sidebar.backToHome":"Terug naar Home","spec-driven-development.sidebar.title":"Spec-Driven Development","spec-driven-development.sidebar.step1":"Wat is Spec-Driven Development?","spec-driven-development.sidebar.step2":"Specs schrijven met Copilot","spec-driven-development.sidebar.step3":"Introductie van GitHub Spec Kit","spec-driven-development.sidebar.step4":"De Spec Kit-workflow","spec-driven-development.sidebar.step5":"Hands-on: bouw een feature spec-first","spec-driven-development.progress.label":"Voortgang","spec-driven-development.step1.duration":"15 minuten","spec-driven-development.step2.duration":"20 minuten","spec-driven-development.step3.duration":"20 minuten","spec-driven-development.step4.duration":"25 minuten","spec-driven-development.step5.duration":"30 minuten","spec-driven-development.stepNav.aria":"Stapnavigatie","spec-driven-development.step5.nextAgentic":"Volgende: Agentic Workflows","spec-driven-development.step1.span1":"Stap 1 van 5","spec-driven-development.step1.title":"Wat is Spec-Driven Development?","spec-driven-development.step1.p2":"Spec-Driven Development (SDD) draait de gebruikelijke AI-codingworkflow om. In plaats van een agent te prompten met \"bouw het gewoon\" en te hopen dat het resultaat bij je bedoeling past, leg je eerst in een duidelijke specificatie vast <strong>wat</strong> je wilt en <strong>waarom</strong> — daarna laat je Copilot die spec omzetten in een plan, tasks en code.","spec-driven-development.step1.h21":"Intentie versus implementatie","spec-driven-development.step1.p3":"Traditioneel prompten mengt intentie en implementatie in één wegwerpbericht. Spec-gedreven ontwikkeling scheidt ze:","spec-driven-development.step1.li1":"<strong>Intentie (de spec)</strong> — De duurzame beschrijving van het probleem, het gewenste gedrag, constraints en acceptatiecriteria. Deze wordt gereviewd, geversioneerd en gedeeld.","spec-driven-development.step1.li2":"<strong>Implementatie (de code)</strong> — Een gevolg van de spec, gegenereerd door de agent en opnieuw gegenereerd wanneer de spec verandert.","spec-driven-development.step1.p4":"Wanneer de spec de source of truth is, wordt code makkelijker opnieuw te genereren, te reviewen en te beredeneren — en heeft de AI een stabiel doel om op te richten.","spec-driven-development.step1.h22":"Waarom specs belangrijk zijn voor AI-coding","spec-driven-development.step1.li3":"<strong>Betere resultaten</strong> — Agents presteren veel beter met expliciete requirements dan met vage oneliners.","spec-driven-development.step1.li4":"<strong>Gedeeld begrip</strong> — Een spec kan door mensen worden gereviewd voordat er ook maar één regel code is geschreven.","spec-driven-development.step1.li5":"<strong>Reproduceerbaarheid</strong> — Dezelfde spec kan consistente regeneratie aansturen over modellen en sessies heen.","spec-driven-development.step1.li6":"<strong>Guardrails</strong> — Constraints en acceptatiecriteria voorkomen dat de agent buiten scope afdwaalt.","spec-driven-development.step1.strong1":"Mentaal model","spec-driven-development.step1.p5":"Zie de spec als het <em>contract</em> en de agent als de <em>aannemer</em>. Je verfijnt het contract totdat het ondubbelzinnig is; de aannemer bouwt op basis daarvan.","spec-driven-development.step1.h23":"Wanneer gebruik je SDD","spec-driven-development.step1.li7":"<strong>Gebruik het</strong> voor nieuwe features, wijzigingen in meerdere bestanden en alles wat je moet reviewen, overdragen of later opnieuw bekijken.","spec-driven-development.step1.li8":"<strong>Sla het over</strong> voor triviale edits, snelle experimenten of fixes van één regel waarbij de overhead het niet waard is.","spec-driven-development.step1.h24":"De SDD-loop","spec-driven-development.step1.li9":"<strong>Specify</strong> — Beschrijf wat en waarom (niet hoe).","spec-driven-development.step1.li10":"<strong>Plan</strong> — Laat Copilot een technische aanpak voorstellen.","spec-driven-development.step1.li11":"<strong>Break down</strong> — Splits het plan op in concrete, geordende tasks.","spec-driven-development.step1.li12":"<strong>Implement</strong> — Voer de tasks uit en verifieer tegen de acceptatiecriteria.","spec-driven-development.step1.p6":"In de volgende stappen oefen je deze loop eerst met gewone Copilot en daarna met <strong>GitHub Spec Kit</strong> — een toolkit die elke fase formaliseert met slash commands.","spec-driven-development.step1.strong2":"Probeer het (2 min): intentie versus implementatie","spec-driven-development.step1.p7":"Neem een feature die je onlangs hebt gebouwd en schrijf één zin die de <em>intentie</em> beschrijft (het wat en waarom), met <strong>nul</strong> verwijzingen naar <em>hoe</em> die is gebouwd. Als je het noemen van een functie, framework of datastructuur niet kunt vermijden, herschrijf het dan. Dit is de spier die SDD traint.","spec-driven-development.step2.span1":"Stap 2 van 5","spec-driven-development.step2.title":"Specs schrijven met Copilot","spec-driven-development.step2.p2":"Voordat je naar specifieke tooling grijpt, kun je spec-gedreven ontwikkeling oefenen met niet meer dan een markdownbestand en GitHub Copilot. Het doel: een spec die precies genoeg is zodat Copilot die zonder giswerk kan implementeren.","spec-driven-development.step2.h21":"Anatomie van een goede spec","spec-driven-development.step2.p3":"Een nuttige feature-spec is gestructureerd en testbaar. Een eenvoudig template:","spec-driven-development.step2.strong1":"Beschrijf wat, niet hoe","spec-driven-development.step2.p4":"Houd specs gericht op gedrag en uitkomsten. Laat implementatiedetails (frameworks, bestandsindeling, algoritmen) over aan de planningsstap, zodat de agent de beste fit voor je codebase kan kiezen.","spec-driven-development.step2.h22":"Gebruik Plan Mode om een spec om te zetten in een plan","spec-driven-development.step2.p5":"Copilot <strong>Plan Mode</strong> leest je spec en de omliggende codebase en stelt daarna een implementatieplan voor dat je kunt reviewen <em>voordat</em> er code wordt geschreven. Dit is de brug tussen intentie en implementatie.","spec-driven-development.step2.li1":"Open je repository in VS Code met het spec-bestand zichtbaar.","spec-driven-development.step2.li2":"Start een Copilot Chat-sessie in Plan Mode en verwijs naar de spec: <code>Plan the implementation of #file:cart-discounts.md</code>","spec-driven-development.step2.li3":"Review de voorgestelde stappen, geef tegengas op alles wat niet past en itereer totdat het plan overeenkomt met je intentie.","spec-driven-development.step2.h23":"Leg conventies vast met instructiebestanden","spec-driven-development.step2.p6":"Specs beschrijven één feature; <strong>instructions files</strong> beschrijven hoe <em>al</em> het werk in de repo moet worden gedaan. Samen geven ze de agent zowel het \"wat\" als de \"huisregels\".","spec-driven-development.step2.strong2":"Probeer het (3 min): scherp één acceptatiecriterium aan","spec-driven-development.step2.p7":"Bekijk de discount-code-spec hierboven. Voeg <strong>één</strong> extra acceptatiecriterium toe dat een edge case vastlegt die nu ontbreekt (bijvoorbeeld: wat gebeurt er wanneer een code wordt toegepast op een lege cart?). Formuleer het als een concrete, controleerbare bewering — een waarde erin, een waarde eruit.","spec-driven-development.step2.p8":"Je kunt guidance ook scopen met pad-specifieke <code>.instructions.md</code>-bestanden, zodat verschillende delen van de codebase verschillende regels volgen.","spec-driven-development.step2.h24":"Oefening: schrijf en plan een spec","spec-driven-development.step2.li4":"Maak <code>specs/feature.md</code> met het template hierboven voor een kleine feature in een voorbeeldrepo.","spec-driven-development.step2.li5":"Voeg een <code>.github/copilot-instructions.md</code> toe met 3–4 conventies voor de repo.","spec-driven-development.step2.li6":"Vraag Copilot in Plan Mode om de implementatie vanuit je spec te plannen.","spec-driven-development.step2.li7":"Verfijn de spec totdat het gegenereerde plan klopt — merk op hoe duidelijkere specs betere plans opleveren.","spec-driven-development.step3.span1":"Stap 3 van 5","spec-driven-development.step3.title":"Introductie van GitHub Spec Kit","spec-driven-development.step3.p2":"<a href=\"https://github.com/github/spec-kit\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub Spec Kit</a> is een open-source toolkit die de spec-gedreven loop omzet in een herhaalbare workflow. Het voegt een set slash commands toe aan je AI-codingagent en een projectstructuur die specs, plans en tasks georganiseerd houdt.","spec-driven-development.step3.h21":"Wat Spec Kit je biedt","spec-driven-development.step3.li1":"<strong>Een consistente structuur</strong> — Toegewijde locaties voor je project constitution, specs, plans en task lists.","spec-driven-development.step3.li2":"<strong>Slash commands</strong> — <code>/speckit.constitution</code>, <code>/speckit.specify</code>, <code>/speckit.plan</code>, <code>/speckit.tasks</code> en <code>/speckit.implement</code> die elke fase van de loop aansturen.","spec-driven-development.step3.li3":"<strong>Agent-agnostic</strong> — Werkt met GitHub Copilot en meer dan 30 andere coding agents.","spec-driven-development.step3.strong1":"Vereisten","spec-driven-development.step3.li4":"<strong>Python 3.11+</strong> en <a href=\"https://docs.astral.sh/uv/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><code>uv</code></a> geïnstalleerd","spec-driven-development.step3.li5":"<strong>Git</strong> en een agent met <strong>GitHub Copilot</strong> ingeschakeld (bijv. VS Code of Copilot CLI)","spec-driven-development.step3.h22":"Installeer de specify CLI en initialiseer een project","spec-driven-development.step3.p3":"Installeer de <code>specify</code> CLI met <code>uv</code>, scaffold daarna een project en kies je agent met <code>--integration</code>. Vervang <code>vX.Y.Z</code> door de nieuwste <a href=\"https://github.com/github/spec-kit/releases\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">release tag</a>:","spec-driven-development.step3.p4":"Spec Kit voegt de <code>/speckit.*</code>-commands toe en een <code>.specify/</code> + <code>specs/</code>-structuur. In IDE-agents verschijnen de commands als slash commands; in <strong>GitHub Copilot CLI</strong> selecteer je de agent met <code>/agents</code> (of spreek je die direct aan in een prompt).","spec-driven-development.step3.h23":"Definieer de project-constitution","spec-driven-development.step3.p5":"De <strong>constitution</strong> legt de niet-onderhandelbare principes vast die je project altijd moet volgen — kwaliteitslatten, architectuurregels en testverwachtingen. De agent raadpleegt deze tijdens planning en implementatie.","spec-driven-development.step3.p6":"Spec Kit schrijft deze principes naar een constitution-bestand, zodat elke volgende <code>/speckit.plan</code> en <code>/speckit.implement</code> ermee aligned blijft.","spec-driven-development.step3.strong2":"Probeer het (5 min): scaffold en inspecteer","spec-driven-development.step3.p7":"Run <code>specify init</code> op een wegwerpproject en open de gegenereerde mappen <code>.specify/</code> en <code>specs/</code>. Run daarna een <code>/speckit.constitution</code>-command met twee eigen principes en open het resulterende constitution-bestand. Wat heeft Spec Kit toegevoegd dat je niet zelf hebt getypt?","spec-driven-development.step3.strong3":"Constitution versus instructions","spec-driven-development.step3.p8":"Een Spec Kit constitution vervult een vergelijkbare rol als een <code>copilot-instructions.md</code>-bestand — projectbrede regels — maar is verweven met de gestructureerde planningscommands van Spec Kit, zodat de principes in elke fase worden afgedwongen.","spec-driven-development.step4.span1":"Stap 4 van 5","spec-driven-development.step4.title":"De Spec Kit-workflow","spec-driven-development.step4.p2":"Met een constitution op zijn plek stuurt Spec Kit de rest van de loop aan via de <code>/speckit.*</code>-commands. Elke command produceert een reviewbaar artifact dat je kunt verfijnen voordat je verdergaat.","spec-driven-development.step4.h21":"/speckit.specify — Beschrijf wat en waarom","spec-driven-development.step4.p3":"Begin met de feature, gericht op intentie in plaats van de tech stack. Spec Kit genereert een gestructureerd specificatiebestand.","spec-driven-development.step4.h22":"/speckit.plan — Kies de technische aanpak","spec-driven-development.step4.p4":"Geef nu je stack en constraints op. Spec Kit maakt een technisch plan dat zowel je spec als je constitution respecteert.","spec-driven-development.step4.h23":"/speckit.tasks — Splits het plan op in stappen","spec-driven-development.step4.p5":"Splits het plan op in een geordende, uitvoerbare task list. Hier wordt het werk concreet en traceerbaar.","spec-driven-development.step4.p6":"Review de gegenereerde tasks op correcte volgorde en dependencies. Herschik of splits alles wat te groot is voordat je implementeert.","spec-driven-development.step4.h24":"/speckit.implement — Voer de tasks uit","spec-driven-development.step4.p7":"Laat de agent de task list doorwerken en de feature bouwen tegen de spec en constitution aan.","spec-driven-development.step4.strong1":"Itereer op het juiste niveau","spec-driven-development.step4.p8":"Als er iets mis is, fix dan het <em>vroegste</em> artifact dat fout is — werk de spec bij, plan opnieuw, genereer tasks opnieuw — in plaats van gegenereerde code met de hand te patchen. De spec als source of truth houden is wat de workflow herhaalbaar maakt.","spec-driven-development.step4.h25":"Optionele kwaliteitscommands","spec-driven-development.step4.p9":"Spec Kit voegt commands toe die werken als \"unit tests voor je spec\" — gebruik ze om gaten te vinden voordat je code genereert:","spec-driven-development.step4.li1":"<code>/speckit.clarify</code> — Breng ondergespecificeerde gebieden naar boven en los ze op (run <em>vóór</em> <code>/speckit.plan</code>).","spec-driven-development.step4.li2":"<code>/speckit.analyze</code> — Consistentie &amp; dekking over artifacts heen controleren (run na <code>/speckit.tasks</code>, vóór <code>/speckit.implement</code>).","spec-driven-development.step4.li3":"<code>/speckit.checklist</code> — Genereer een aangepaste kwaliteitschecklist die completeness, duidelijkheid en consistentie van requirements valideert.","spec-driven-development.step4.strong2":"Probeer het (5 min): één command geïsoleerd","spec-driven-development.step4.p10":"Oefen vóór de volledige hands-on één fase op zichzelf. Run in een project dat al een spec heeft alleen <code>/speckit.tasks</code> en lees de gegenereerde task list. Staan de tasks in de juiste volgorde? Is één task te groot om veilig te implementeren? Herschik of splits er één voordat je verdergaat.","spec-driven-development.step4.h26":"De volledige loop in één oogopslag","spec-driven-development.step5.span1":"Stap 5 van 5","spec-driven-development.step5.title":"Hands-on: bouw een feature spec-first","spec-driven-development.step5.p2":"Breng de volledige loop samen. Je brengt een kleine feature van idee naar werkende code, volledig spec-first, met Spec Kit.","spec-driven-development.step5.h21":"De uitdaging","spec-driven-development.step5.p3":"Bouw een <strong>command-line \"habit tracker\"</strong> waarmee een gebruiker dagelijkse habits kan toevoegen, ze voor vandaag als voltooid kan markeren en een wekelijkse streak-samenvatting kan bekijken. Geen UI-framework nodig — houd het simpel.","spec-driven-development.step5.h22":"Stap voor stap","spec-driven-development.step5.li1":"<strong>Initialize</strong> een nieuw project met <code>specify init habit-tracker --integration copilot</code>.","spec-driven-development.step5.li2":"<strong>/speckit.constitution</strong> — Vereis unit tests voor alle logica, geen externe dependencies buiten de standaardbibliotheek en duidelijke help-output.","spec-driven-development.step5.li3":"<strong>/speckit.specify</strong> — Beschrijf het gedrag en de acceptatiecriteria van de habit tracker (toevoegen, voltooien, wekelijkse streak). Focus op wat, niet hoe.","spec-driven-development.step5.li4":"<strong>/speckit.plan</strong> — Kies een taal (bijv. Python of Node), een storage-aanpak (een lokaal JSON-bestand) en een eenvoudige command-structuur.","spec-driven-development.step5.li5":"<strong>/speckit.tasks</strong> — Genereer de task list en review de volgorde.","spec-driven-development.step5.li6":"<strong>/speckit.implement</strong> — Laat de agent het bouwen en run daarna de app en tests.","spec-driven-development.step5.h23":"Acceptatiecriteria om te verifiëren","spec-driven-development.step5.li7":"Een habit toevoegen blijft bewaard tussen runs.","spec-driven-development.step5.li8":"Een habit twee keer op één dag als voltooid markeren is idempotent.","spec-driven-development.step5.li9":"De wekelijkse samenvatting toont de juiste huidige streak per habit.","spec-driven-development.step5.li10":"Alle logica is gedekt door geslaagde unit tests.","spec-driven-development.step5.strong1":"Reflectie","spec-driven-development.step5.p4":"Wanneer een criterium faalt, weersta dan de neiging om de code handmatig te editen. Werk de spec of het plan bij en genereer opnieuw. Merk op hoeveel sneller iteratie wordt wanneer de spec — niet de code — je source of truth is.","spec-driven-development.step5.h31":"Wat is de volgende stap?","spec-driven-development.step5.li11":"Voeg een nieuwe requirement toe aan de spec (bijv. reminders) en zie hoe één pass met <code>/speckit.plan</code> → <code>/speckit.tasks</code> → <code>/speckit.implement</code> de app uitbreidt.","spec-driven-development.step5.li12":"Combineer SDD met het <a href=\"agentic-workflows.html\">Agentic Workflows</a>-pad om spec-gedreven wijzigingen in CI te automatiseren.","spec-driven-development.step5.li13":"Breng Spec Kit in een echte repository en probeer het uit op je volgende feature.","spec-driven-development.step5.h32":"Bronnen","spec-driven-development.step5.li14":"<a href=\"https://github.com/github/spec-kit\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub Spec Kit-repository</a>","spec-driven-development.step5.li15":"<a href=\"https://github.blog/ai-and-ml/generative-ai/spec-driven-development-with-ai-get-started-with-a-new-open-source-toolkit/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Spec-driven development met AI (GitHub Blog)</a>","spec-driven-development.step5.li16":"<a href=\"https://docs.github.com/copilot\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub Copilot-documentatie</a>","spec-driven-development.step5.li17":"<a href=\"https://docs.astral.sh/uv/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">uv / uvx-documentatie</a>"});
})();
